The Age of Liberty: Sweden, 1719-1772 |year= 1986}}\n* {{cite book |last= Scott |first= Franklin D. |title= Sweden: The Nation's History |year= 1988 |publisher= Southern Illinois University Press |edition= 2nd |isbn= 0-8093-1489-4 |url= https://archive.org/details/swedennationshis00fran }} (survey by leading scholar)\n* {{cite book |last= Sprague |first= Martina |title= Sweden: An Illustrated History |year=2005 |publisher= Hippocrene Books |isbn= 0-7818-1114-7 }}\n* Stadin, Kekke. \"The masculine image of a great power: Representations of Swedish imperial power c. 1630\u20131690.\" ''Scandinavian journal of history'' 30.1 (2005): 61\u201382.\n* {{cite book |last= Warme |first= Lars G. |title= A History of Swedish Literature |year= 1995 }}\n\n{{Sweden topics}}\n{{Empires}}\n{{History of Europe}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Swedish Empire}}\n[[Category:Swedish Empire| ]]\n[[Category:Early Modern history of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Former empires in Europe]]\n[[Category:Finland under Swedish rule]]\n[[Category:17th century in Sweden]]\n[[Category:18th century in Sweden]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1611]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1721]]\n[[Category:1611 establishments in Sweden]]\n[[Category:1721 disestablishments in Sweden]]\n[[Category:1611 establishments in Europe]]\n[[Category:1721 disestablishments in Europe]]\n[[Category:History of Sweden by period]]\n", "name_user": "SergeWoodzing", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swedish_Empire"}
