31992)\n* [[John Smith (Labour Party leader)|John Smith]] (1992\u20131994)\n** [[Margaret Beckett]] (1994; acting)<ref name=\"rule\">{{cite journal|url=http://researchbriefings.files.parliament.uk/documents/SN03938/SN03938.pdf|title=Labour Party Rule Book 2014|publisher=House of Commons Library|quote=When the party is in opposition and the party leader, for whatever reason, becomes permanently unavailable, the deputy leader shall automatically become party leader on a pro-tem basis.|journal=|access-date=26 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025093405/http://researchbriefings.files.parliament.uk/documents/SN03938/SN03938.pdf|archive-date=25 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Tony Blair]] (1994\u20132007)\n* [[Gordon Brown]] (2007\u20132010)\n** [[Harriet Harman]] (2010; acting)<ref name=\"rule\"/>\n* [[Ed Miliband]] (2010\u20132015)\n** [[Harriet Harman]] (2015; acting)\n* [[Jeremy Corbyn]] ([[2015 Labour Party leadership election (UK)|2015]]\u2013[[2020 Labour Party leadership election|2020]])\n* [[Sir Keir Starmer]] (2020\u2013present){{div col end}}\n\n=== Living former Labour Party leaders ===\n{{As of|2017|02}}, there are six living former Labour Party leaders.\n<gallery class=\"centre\">\nFile:Kinnock, Neil.jpg|[[Neil Kinnock]]<br>(1983\u20131992)<br>born 1942 (age {{age|1942|3|28}})\nFile:Official portrait of Margaret Beckett crop 2.jpg|[[Margaret Beckett]]<br>(1994; interim)<br>born 1943 (age {{age|1943|1|15}})\nFile:MSC 2014 Blair Mueller MSC2014 (cropped).jpg|[[Tony Blair]]<br>([[Premiership of Tony Blair|1994\u20132007]])<br>born 1953 (age {{age|1953|5|6}})\nFile:Gordon Brown official.jpg|[[Gordon Brown]]<br>([[Premiership of Gordon Brown|2007\u20132010]])<br>born 1951 (age {{age|1951|2|20}})\nFile:Harriet Harman.jpg|[[Harriet Harman]]<br>(2010 and 2015; interim)<br>born 1950 (age {{age|1950|7|30}})\nFile:Official portrait of Edward Miliband crop 2 retouch.jpg|[[Ed Miliband]]<br>(2010\u20132015)<br>born 1969 (age {{age|1969|12|24}})\n</gallery>\n\n=== Deputy Leaders of the Labour Party since 1922 ===\n{{main|Deputy Leader of the Labour Party (UK)}}\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[John Robert Clynes]] (1922\u20131932)\n* [[William Graham (Edinburgh MP)|William Graham]] (1931\u20131932)\n* [[Clement Attlee]] (1932\u20131935)\n* [[Arthur Greenwood]] (1935\u20131945)\n* [[Herbert Morrison]] (1945\u20131955)\n* [[Jim Griffiths]] (1955\u20131959)\n* [[Aneurin Bevan]] (1959\u20131960)\n* [[George Brown, Baron George-Brown|George Brown]] (1960\u20131970)\n* [[Roy Jenkins]] (1970\u20131972)\n* [[Edward Short, Baron Glenamara|Edward Short]] (1972\u20131976)\n* [[Michael Foot]] (1976\u20131980)\n* [[Denis Healey]] (1980\u20131983)\n* [[Roy Hattersley]] (1983\u20131992)\n* [[Margaret Beckett]] (1992\u20131994)\n* [[John Prescott]] (1994\u20132007)\n* [[Harriet Harman]] (2007\u20132015)\n* [[Tom Watson (Labour politician)|Tom Watson]] (2015\u20132019)\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Living former Labour Party deputy leaders ===\nAs of {{Monthyear}}, there are five [[Deputy Leader of the Labour Party (UK)|living former Labour Party deputy leaders]].\n<gallery class=\"centre\">\nFile:Roy Hattersley 2012 cropped 2.jpg|[[Roy Hattersley]]<br>(1983\u20131992)<br>born 1932 (age {{age|1932|12|28}})\nFile:Official portrait of Margaret Beckett crop 2.jpg|[[Margaret Beckett]]<br>(1992\u20131994)<br>born 1943 (age {{age|1943|1|15}})\nFile:John Prescott on his last day as Deputy Prime Minister, June 2007 cropped.jpg|[[John Prescott]]<br>(1994\u20132007)<br>born 1938 (age {{age|1938|5|31}})\nFile:Harriet Harman.jpg|[[Harriet Harman]]<br>(2007\u20132015)<br>born 1950 (age {{age|1950|7|30}})\nFile:Official_portrait_of_Tom_Watson_crop_2.jpg|[[Tom Watson (Labour politician)|Tom Watson]]<br>(2015\u20132019)<br>born 1967 (age {{age|1967|1|8}})\n</gallery>\n\n=== Leaders in the House of Lords since 1924 ===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Richard Haldane, 1st Viscount Haldane]] (1924\u20131928)\n* [[Charles Cripps, 1st Baron Par