 political party/seats|202|650|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 60\n|31.1\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|{{no2|Conservative}}\n|}\n[[File:Popular vote.jpg|thumb|upright=1.35|A graph showing the percentage of the popular vote received by major parties in general elections (1832\u20132005)]]\n; Note:\n{{reflist|group=\"fn\"}}\n\n==== European Parliament elections ====\n{{see also|European Parliament|Elections to the European Parliament}}\nElections to the European Parliament began in 1979, and were held under the [[First-past-the-post voting|first past the post]] system until 1999, when a form of [[proportional representation]] was introduced.\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Leader\n!% share of votes\n!Seats\n!Change\n!Position\n|-\n|[[1979 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1979]]\n|{{sortname|James|Callaghan}}\n|31.6\n|{{composition bar|17|78|#DA251D}}\n|\n|2nd\n|-\n|[[1984 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1984]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{sortname|Neil|Kinnock}}\n|34.7\n|{{composition bar|32|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 15\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[1989 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1989]]\n|40.1\n|{{composition bar|45|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 13\n|{{increase}} 1st\n|-\n|[[1994 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1994]]\n|{{sortname|Margaret|Beckett}}<br>(interim)\n|42.6\n|{{composition bar|62|84|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 17\n|{{steady}} 1st\n|-\n|[[1999 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1999]]<ref group=\"fn\">Electoral system changed from first past the post to proportional representation.</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{sortname|Tony|Blair}}\n|28.0\n|{{composition bar|29|84|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 33\n|{{decrease}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2004]]\n|22.6\n|{{composition bar|19|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 6\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2009 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2009]]\n|{{sortname|Gordon|Brown}}\n|15.7\n|{{composition bar|13|72|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 5\n|{{decrease}} 3rd\n|-\n|[[2014 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2014]]\n|{{sortname|Ed|Miliband}}\n|24.4\n|{{composition bar|20|73|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 7\n|{{increase}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2019 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2019]]\n|{{sortname|Jeremy|Corbyn}}\n|13.6\n|{{composition bar|10|73|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 10\n|{{decrease}} 3rd\n|}\n; Note:\n{{reflist|group=\"fn\"}}\n\n=== Devolved assembly elections ===\n==== Scottish Parliament elections ====\n{{see also|Scottish Parliament|Scottish Labour Party}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Leader\n!% share of votes<br>(constituency)\n!% share of votes<br>(list)\n!Seats\n!Change\n!Position\n!Resulting government\n|-\n|[[1999 Scottish Parliament election|1999]]\n|{{sortname|Donald|Dewar}}\n|38.8\n|33.6\n|{{composition bar|56|129|#DA251D}}\n|\n|'''1st'''\n|style=\"background-color:#CCFFCC\"|Labour\u2013[[Scottish Liberal Democrats|Liberal Democrats]]\n|-\n|[[2003 Scottish Parliament election|2003]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{sortname|Jack|McConnell}}\n|34.6\n|29.3\n|{{composition bar|50|129|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 6\n|{{steady}} '''1st'''\n|style=\"background-color:#CCFFCC\"|Labour\u2013Liberal Democrats\n|-\n|[[2007 Scottish Parliament election|2007]]\n|32.2\n|29.2\n|{{composition bar|46|129|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 4\n|{{decrease}} 2nd\n|style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"|[[Scottish National Party|Scottish National]] minority\n|-\n|[[2011 Scottish Parliament election|2011]]\n|{{sortname|Iain|Gray}}\n|31.7\n|26.3\n|{{composition bar|37|129|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 7\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"|Scottish National\n|-\n|[[2016 Scottish Parliament election|2016]]\n|{{sortname|Kezia|Dugdale}}\n|22.6\n|19.1\n|{{composition bar|24|129|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 13\n|{{decrease}} 3rd\n|style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"|Scottish National minority\n|}\n\n==== Welsh Assembly elec